    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Carbon dioxide used in its liquid state as a non-toxic, environmentally friendly solvent for cleaning, degreasing, and decontaminating materials. Liquid carbon dioxide is also used to promote plant growth in a greenhouse environment, and, stored under pressure in a tank, as a carbon dioxide fire extinguisher. And has been used in the treatment of ethnological and natural history museum collections. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
